Name: leukocyte adhesion deficiency 2
Definition: A leukocyte adhesion deficiency that is characterized by the absence of Sialyl Lewis X of E-selectin resulting in recurrent bacterial infections

Name: leukocyte adhesion deficiency 1
Definition: A leukocyte adhesion deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation of the ITGB2 gene on chromosome 21q22.3.

Name: leukocyte adhesion deficiency 3
Definition: A leukocyte adhesion deficiency that is characterized by a defect in beta integrins 1
